</p>

</div>
<div id="fn" class="footnote"><a class="note-ref" href="#PJA11d070n1-ptr" id="PJA11d070n1">1</a>

   <p><abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr> refers to Mouffle dAngervilles <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Vie prive de Louis XV, ou principaux vnemens, particularits et anecdotes de son rgne</span>, 4 vols., London, 1781, a copy of which is in <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s library at the Boston Public Library (<span class="ref-st" title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ &lt;i&gt;Catalogue of the John Adams Library in the Public Library of the City of Boston&lt;/i&gt;, Boston, 1917. ]"><span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Catalogue of <abbr title="fade=[ on ] fadespeed=[0.1] windowlock=[on] cssbody=[ boxover ] header=[]  body=[ John Adams (17351826) ]">JA</abbr>s Library</span></span>). Robert Lovelace was the unscrupulous rake who courted the title character in Samuel Richardsons <span class="hi-italic" style="font-style: italic;">Clarissa Harlowe</span> and brought both to a bad end.</p>

